pullRequest.bodyText:
Pull Request template
Purpose / Description
5816  Call Show Answer / displayCardAnswer() funtion from AnkiDroid card webview using javascript
After implementing HanziWriter.js in Ankidroid. Check Anki-maobi . I came to know that user have to manually click show answer. But I wanted that after completion of drawing stroke of characters, It automatically move to next card or show back side of card.
Also I want to implement showAnswer for Ease_1, Ease_2, Ease_3, Ease_4 as per user done mistake in drawing strokes of characters.
Fixes
#5816
Approach
Automatic showAnswer() function to be called by javascript

Added the following in card.js in assets folder

/* function to show answer using js */
function showAnswer() {
    window.location.href = "signal:show_answer";
}
function buttonAnswerEase1() {
    window.location.href = "signal:answer_ease1";
}
function buttonAnswerEase2() {
    window.location.href = "signal:answer_ease2";
}
function buttonAnswerEase3() {
    window.location.href = "signal:answer_ease3";
}
function buttonAnswerEase4() {
    window.location.href = "signal:answer_ease4";
}


I added following to webview in AbstractFlashcardViewer.java to filterUrl()

/*show answer using js functions*/
                if("signal:show_answer".equals(url)){
                    if (!sDisplayAnswer) {
                        displayCardAnswer();
                    }
                    return true;
                }
                if("signal:answer_ease1".equals(url)){
                    if (sDisplayAnswer) {
                        answerCard(EASE_1);
                    } else {
                        displayCardAnswer();
                    }
                    return true;
                }
                if("signal:answer_ease2".equals(url)){
                    if (sDisplayAnswer) {
                        answerCard(EASE_2);
                    } else {
                        displayCardAnswer();
                    }
                    return true;
                }
                if("signal:answer_ease3".equals(url)){
                    if (sDisplayAnswer) {
                        answerCard(EASE_3);
                    } else {
                        displayCardAnswer();
                    }
                    return true;
                }
                if("signal:answer_ease4".equals(url)){
                    if (sDisplayAnswer) {
                        answerCard(EASE_4);
                    } else {
                        displayCardAnswer();
                    }
                    return true;
                }



After that I called the showAnswer function from front side of deck in Ankidroid

{{Front}}
<input type="button" value="Show Answer" onclick="showAnswer();"/>

How Has This Been Tested?
I have testes it in android emulator.
To test:-

Start review deck
Select deck
Then click three dot then, click Edit Note
Then click at bottom Cards: Card 1
Add following to Front template
For Show Answer

{{Front}}
<input type="button" value="Show Answer" onclick="showAnswer(); return false;"/>

For showing Ease_1 answer / Again
<input type="button" value="Ease 1" onclick="buttonAnswerEase1(); return false;"/>

For showing Ease_2 answer / Hard
<input type="button" value="Ease 2" onclick="buttonAnswerEase2(); return false;"/>

For showing Ease_3 answer / Good
<input type="button" value="Ease 3" onclick="buttonAnswerEase3(); return false;"/>

For showing Ease_4 answer / Easy
<input type="button" value="Ease 4" onclick="buttonAnswerEase4(); return false;"/>


Then javascript button can show answers.

Benefits of using this, Show Answer called automatically after completion of answer typed or drawed after validation.
For ex:- I have implemeted existing hanzi writer js in in Ankidroid. In that after completion of drawing stroke of charactes, user have to manually type Show Answer button.
But if it get added to Ankidroid then It will be more useful.
